for me when i'm working on something and
i'm really into it and i start to enter
the flow state it's almost as if time
and space
become irrelevant like i'm seabiscuit
galloping across the dirt with blinders
on all the stars have aligned and my
body and my mind have synergized into
one common goal and for that moment i am
fulfilling my purpose as my brain
chemistry ignites and lights off
thousands of fireworks inside my head
that trickle down my spine enter all of
my nerves into my hands like a super
highway of blood vessels and nerve
endings all working together to perform
what i've been searching for leading up
to that point and once it strikes it
feels
so right like it's where i belong and
that i'm doing all the right things
because we as creators are meant to
create in this little pocket of what i
like to perceive as altered reality is
the sweet spot and these little rare
moments collected over time is where we
create our best work and where we are
truly allowed to give ourselves
permission to make the strongest
connections both with ourselves
and with our audience when you get into
that flow state that's the magic of
creating and that's why we do it and
that's why it's so important to give
yourself time to enter the flow state
because not only do you owe it to
yourself but you owe it to everyone else
who's going to benefit from the things
that you created
in that altered reality
